    "description": "The Bank Of Kochi, Ltd. provides various banking products and services in Japan. It operates in three segments: Banking Business, Leasing Business, and Credit Card Business. The company offers deposit and comprehensive accounts; inheritance-only and retirement benefit-only fixed term, and foreign currency deposits; tax-free small investment system; investment; accumulation investment and investment trusts; pension periodic payment; term-asset management; and government and private placement bonds. It also provides loan products, including free, car, housing, card, reverse mortgage, educational, and business loans, as well as loan consultation; insurance products, such as medical and cancer, individual pension, property, whole life, and term insurance; guardianship system support deposit; trust contract agency business; individual-type defined contribution pension plan; testamentary trust and estate settlement services; dedicated account for educational donations; and inheritance procedures. In addition, the company offers services comprising internet banking, payment and transfer, electronic money and smartphone payment, payroll transfer, foreign exchange and remittance, pension receipt, telephone, and ATM functions, as well as EB, web transfer reception, bank deposit, and various seminars and consultations. Further, it provides business support services, which include digitization, merger and acquisition, financial diagnostics, industry-academia collaboration, employee benefits, and sales channel expansion and business matching; international business trade transactions; securities investment; and leasing operations. The company serves individual, corporate, and sole proprietor customers. The Bank Of Kochi, Ltd. was incorporated in 1930 and is headquartered in Kochi, Japan."
